tourBios.curYrHigh: Posted rounds of 74-67-67-70 to claim medalist honors at the Sebring, FL Q-School and secure exempt status for the season on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica… Went bogey-free for a first round leading 9-under 63 at the season opening 69th Avianca Colombia Open presented by BBVA, an event he finished solo third in Rionegro, Colombia in February.
tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Made four Web.com Tour starts, all in August. Played the weekend in the last three, finishing T23 at the Price Cutter Charity Championship, T13 at the News Sentinel Open and T26 at the WinCo Foods Portland Open. All but three of his 14 rounds were in the 60s...Playing on a sponsor's exemption, finished T12 at the Mackenzie Tour's Syncrude Boreal Open, with rounds of 72-69-68-68...Finished third at the Staal Foundation Open in Thunder Bay.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Finished runner-up at the 2014 U.S. Amateur, earning a spot in the 2015 Masters Tournament…Named the 2013-14 Co-MAC Player of the Year along with Kent State teammate Taylor Pendrith. Recorded four wins while playing for the Golden Flashes…Won the 2014 Jones Cup… Won the 2010 Ontario Amateur.
tourBios.personal: Dream foursome would include his dad, Mike Weir and Tiger Woods.. Most memorable moment in golf was finishing fourth at the 2012 NCAA Championship and competing in the match-play portion of the tournament.

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Began the year with no status but secured several sponsor's exemptions as an alumnus of Golf Canada's National Amateur Team...One of which was the Staal Foundation Open, where he shared the 54-hole lead and carded a final-round 70 to finish solo third...As one of the top three members on the Order of Merit through the first half of the season, earned status for the remainder of the year...Shot a final-round 65 at The Wildfire Invitational to notch his second top-10 of the season at T10...Ended the season 37th on the Order of Merit to secure exempt status for 2016.
